data.text:
UCL Library Services supports learning, teaching and research at UCL and includes libraries and learning spaces located across London, covering a wide range of specialist subjects. It is also the home of the UCL Office for Open Science and Scholarship.

Using the Library

Getting started, libraries and study spaces, opening hours, borrowing, membership and more.

Finding Resources

Finding and accessing books, journals and electronic resources, in our libraries and beyond.

Learning & Teaching Support

Library skills training, subject-specific support, request new resources, reading lists and copyright assistance.

Open Science & Research Support

Including Open Access, Research Data Management, Bibliometrics and Copyright.

Collections

Modern and Special Collections, digital materials, exhibitions, archives and managing records.

NHS

Information for NHS staff and students about our services.
